Ascension did no receive supplies of the coronation issue until their issue on 19th May 1937
a week after the intended date of issue. the public sent about 30,000 covers to Ascension with a request
for the three values to be affixed to each cover. This was hard work for the limited Post Office clerks and only 2,835 were handled on the date of the issue and into the early hours of the following morning. 
Registered envelopes handled the next morning received the cancellation of the 19th of May and
the registration number applied with the serial counter but without the blue crayon 'R' which was inserted earlier in the operation. The rest of the envelopes were handled over the next four days.

