A few covers exist which were prepared on board the vessel \textit{City of New York} bearing 
the Ascension stamps and cancelled with a circular handstamp reading 'M.V. CITY OF NEW YOR/AMERICAN SOUTH
AFRICAN LINE, Inc'. In the Centre ofthis handstamp, which consisted of concentric circles of 34mm and 24 mm the words 'SEA POST' were added. The date was applied separately reading 'MAY 12th 1937'. These are
forgeries as the records of Lloyds show that this boat was in New York on 19th May!

